ifference head on and sought to bridge the local and the international. In so doing, it enabled indigenous claimants to forge a colonial politics of justice that opened up space for a conversation between colonial rulers and ruled.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 7aHISTORY / Latin America / Mexico.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150362710940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503627109423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781503627109/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles